recipeIngredients:
• Frozen berries, any type, ¾ cup(s) (5.2oz)
  • Whole-wheat English muffin, 1 muffin(s) (2.3oz)
  • Peanut butter, reduced sugar & salt, 2½ tsp(s) (0.5oz)
  • Part-skim ricotta cheese, 3 oz(s) (3oz)
recipeInstructions:
Roughly chop or slice larger berries. Place berries into a small non-stick frying pan with 2 teaspoons of water. Warm berries over medium-high heat for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring often. Remove from the heat and allow to stand for 5 minutes. Alternately, place frozen berries in a microwave-safe dish and microwave them on medium to high for 30 to 60 seconds.

Toast the English muffin. Spread the peanut butter over each muffin half. Top with ricotta and berries. 

TIP: Drizzle over a teaspoon of honey if you have Sweets to spare for the day. Swap the peanut butter for 1.5 tablespoons of chopped peanuts for a crunchier version.

recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 2 tbsp(s) (1oz)
  • Extra lean ground turkey, raw, 6 oz(s) (6oz)
  • Red onion, 1 small, chopped (2.1oz)
  • Green bell pepper, ½ pepper(s), chopped (2oz)
  • Red bell pepper, raw, ½ medium, chopped (2.1oz)
  • Zucchini, 1 small, chopped (4.2oz)
  • Taco seasoning, 2 tbsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Red kidney beans, ⅓ cup(s), rinsed and drained (2.1oz)
  • Low sodium chicken stock, 2 cup(s) (1.1lb)
  • Cauliflower rice, 2 cup(s) (6.9oz)
  • Cilantro, fresh, 1 cup(s) (0.8oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Turkey & bean taco casserole according to recipe instructions below.

Store the cooked turkey and vegetables in a container in the fridge. Store the remaining cauliflower rice and cilantro in separate airtight containers in the fridge for later in the week.

Turkey & bean taco casserole instructions

Heat the oil in a deep non-stick skillet over medium-high heat and add the turkey and onion. Cook, stirring and breaking up any ground turkey lumps with the back of a spoon, for 3 minutes or until the onion is softened but not browned.

Stir in the bell peppers, zucchini, seasoning, beans and stock and bring to a simmer. Simmer, partially covered and stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes. Remove the lid, continue to simmer, uncovered and stirring occasionally, for another 10 minutes or until the vegetables are tender and the stock has reduced by two-thirds.

Heat the cauliflower rice according to packet instructions. Divide the cauliflower rice and casserole between bowls. Top with the cilantro and serve.

recipieName: Spiced steak with salad, parmesan & bread
recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 2 tsp(s) (0.3oz)
  • Paprika, ½ tsp(s), dried
  • Cumin, ground, ½ tsp(s)
  • Parsley, fresh, ½ cup(s), chopped (1.1oz)
  • Garlic, minced, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es), ground
  • Beef tenderloin steak, any grade, very lean, 4 oz(s) (4oz)
  • Baby spinach, 2 handful(s) (1.7oz)
  • Cherry tomatoes, 5 cherry tomato(es), halved (3oz)
  • Red bell pepper, raw, ¼ medium, cut into thin strips (1oz)
  • Carrot, shredded, 4 tbsp(s) (1oz)
  • Grated Parmesan cheese, ⅓ cup(s) (0.9oz)
  • Balsamic vinegar, 1 tbsp(s) (0.6oz)

recipeInstructions:
In a small bowl, combine the oil, paprika, cumin, half the parsley, garlic and black pepper and mix well.

Place the beef in a shallow bowl. Pour over the marinade and toss to coat. If you have time, cover and place in the fridge for 30 mins to marinate.

Heat a non-stick frying pan to medium-high heat and cook steak for 3 to 4 minutes each side, or until cooked to your liking. Remove from the pan and cover.

Meanwhile prepare a quick salad using the spinach, tomatoes, bell pepper and carrot. Sprinkle remaining parsley, parmesan and drizzle with balsamic vinegar.

Serve spiced steak alongside salad and a slice of bread.

TIP: Serve steak with steamed mixed vegetables if preferred.

If you have time available make croutons by toasting bread and allowing to cool. Cut into squares and toss through the salad.

recipeIngredients:
• Old fashioned (rolled) oats, 2 cup(s) (5.6oz)
  • 1% milk, 2 cup(s) (1pt)
  • Pear, 1 small, shredded (5.2oz)
  • Ground nutmeg, 1½ tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Non-fat plain Greek yogurt, 2 cup(s) (16oz)
  • Walnuts, 20 walnut(s), chopped (1.4oz)
  • Sesame seeds, 2 tbsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Frozen berries, any type, 2 cup(s), frozen or fresh (13.9oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare the Overnight oats with berries & pear according to recipe instructions below. 

Portion into 4 separate containers or jars and refrigerate overnight so that you can grab and go in the morning.

When ready to eat, grab one container or jar. Spoon into a bowl, top with ½ cup berries and a quarter of the nut and seed mix. Sprinkle with a pinch of nutmeg if desired.

TIP: For cooler days, warm overnight oats in the microwave.

Overnight oats with berries & pear instructions

Place oats into a bowl or container. Add the milk, pear, nutmeg and yogurt. Stir to combine. Cover and place in the fridge overnight to soak.

To toast walnuts and sesame seeds, heat a small skillet over medium heat. Toast, stirring 2 to 3 minutes until golden being careful not to burn. Remove skillet from heat and allow to cool. Chop walnuts into small pieces. Store nut and seed mix in the fridge in a small airtight container.

When ready to eat, divide oat mixture between four bowls. Top each bowl with half a cup berries and a quarter of the toasted nut and seed mix. Sprinkle with a pinch of nutmeg if desired.

TIP: Prepared overnight oats mix will keep for 5 days in airtight containers in the fridge. Add remaining ingredients when ready to eat. For the nut mix, store in an airtight container in the fridge.

recipieName: Lentils with roast mushrooms & Mediterranean vegetables
recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 4 tsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • White onion, chopped, ⅔ cup(s) (3.7oz)
  • Garlic, minced, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Thyme, fresh, 2 tsp(s), 5 sprigs (0.1oz)
  • Eggplant, ¼ eggplant(s), unpeeled, chopped (4.8oz)
  • Red bell pepper, chopped, ⅓ cup(s) (1.7oz)
  • Zucchini, 1 medium, diced (6.9oz)
  • Tomatoes, canned, 1 can(s) (6.7oz)
  • Lentils, canned, drained, 1 cup(s), rinsed (6.3oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
  • Portabella mushrooms, 2 piece(s), whole (5.9oz)
  • Arugula, 4 cup(s) (2.8oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Lentils with roast mushrooms & Mediterranean vegetables according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for dinner. Store the remaining serving in an airtight container and refrigerate for later in the week.

Lentils with roast mushrooms & Mediterranean vegetables instructions

Preheat oven 400°F. Lightly grease a medium roasting pan.

Heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil in a medium non-stick skillet over medium heat. Add onion and garlic, cook stirring for 3 minutes until soft. Stir in the thyme, eggplant, bell pepper and zucchini. Cook stirring for 2 minutes. Add tomatoes and 1/3 cup of water. Bring to a simmer. Simmer for 3 to 4 minutes until ratatouille thickens slightly. Remove from the heat, stir in the lentils. Season to taste. Spoon into the roasting pan.

Nestle the mushrooms in the ratatouille. Roast for 15 minutes until mushrooms are just tender. Divide into two portions. Spoon remaining 2 teaspoons of oil over the arugula, toss to coat. Scatter the arugula over the mushrooms. Season to taste. Serve.

TIP: If you prefer, you can swap the lentils for 2 poached eggs and serve them on top of the mushrooms and ratatouille.

recipeIngredients:
• Sweet potato, 1 small sweet potato(s), thickly sliced (4.6oz)
  • Eggplant, 1 eggplant(s), unpeeled, thickly sliced (1.2lb)
  • Zucchini, 1 medium, thickly sliced lengthways (6.9oz)
  • Red bell pepper, chopped, ¾ cup(s) (3.9oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 1½ tbsp(s) (0.7oz)
  • Black pepper, 2 dash(es)
  • Whole wheat couscous, 1 cup, cooked (5.5oz)
  • Non-fat plain Greek yogurt, 2 tbsp(s) (1oz)
  • Dijon mustard, 1 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • White wine vinegar, 4 tsp(s) (0.7oz)
  • Parsley, fresh, 2 tbsp(s) (0.3oz)
  • Tuna, canned in water, 6 oz(s), drained, or 2 x 3 oz cans (6oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare the Tuna & roast vegetable salad according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for lunch. Store the remaining serving in an airtight container and refrigerate for later in the week.

Tuna & roast vegetable salad instructions

Preheat oven to 425°F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.

Place the sweet potato, eggplant, zucchini and bell pepper on the prepared baking sheet. Drizzle with olive oil and season to taste. Toss to coat. Roast the vegetables for 20 minutes or until cooked and caramelized. Allow to cool and then transfer to a serving bowl.

Meanwhile, to make the dressing, whisk together yogurt, mustard, white wine vinegar and parsley in a bowl and season to taste with pepper.

Into the bowl with the cooked vegetables, add the cooked couscous and tuna. Drizzle over the dressing and toss gently to combine. To serve, divide the salad between two bowls.

TIP: For cooler days, serve roast vegetables and couscous warm.

recipeIngredients:
• Sesame seeds, 3 tsp(s) (0.3oz)
  • Cumin, ground, 2 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Coriander, ground, 2 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Paprika, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Crushed red pepper flakes, ½ tsp(s)
  • Eggs, 1 large, whisked (1.8oz)
  • Chicken breast, raw, 6 oz(s), 2 x 3 ounce fillets (6oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 1 tbsp(s) (0.5oz)
  • Broccoli florets, 2 cup(s) (5oz)
  • Carrots, 1 medium, cut into 1-inch pieces (2.2oz)
  • Green beans, trimmed, 1 cup(s) (3.5oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Dukkah-crusted chicken according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for dinner. Store the remaining serving of chicken and vegetables in an airtight container in the fridge to enjoy later in the week.

Dukkah-crusted chicken instructions

For the dukkah, scatter the sesame seeds in a small non-stick skillet over medium heat. Cook, shaking skillet for 2 to 3 minutes until the sesame seeds start to color. Add the cumin, coriander, paprika and red pepper flakes, cook while gently shaking the skillet for 1 minute, until spices are warm. Allow to cool.

Place the whisked egg into a bowl and the dukkah into a second bowl. Dip the chicken in the egg and then coat in the dukkah.

Heat the oil in a non-stick skillet over medium heat. Cook the chicken, gently turning after 4 minutes. Cook for a further 3 minutes, or until cooked through and transfer to a plate to rest. Meanwhile, steam the broccoli, carrots and green beans for 3 to 4 miutes, or until cooked to your liking. Season to taste and serve alongside the cooked chicken.

TIP: Make a few servings of the dukkah recipe and store in a jar with a lid.

  • Snow peas, ⅓ cup(s), chopped (1.9oz)

recipeInstructions:
In a small bowl, combine the sweet chili sauce, soy sauce and juice of half a lime. Remove ½ tablespoon of the sweet chili soy mixture into a second small bowl and stir in 1 teaspoon of olive oil and reserve for the dressing. Cover both bowls and set aside.

Heat a medium non-stick skillet or wok over medium-high heat. Add remaining 1 teaspoon of olive oil and ground beef. Cook, stirring for 2 minutes, until beef has browned. Add the sweet chili soy mixture (not the dressing) and stir-fry for 1 minute. Remove from the heat, stir through the snow peas, carrots and green onions.

Spoon into a bowl, top with bean sprouts and cilantro. Drizzle the reserved dressing over the bliss bowl. Serve with lime wedges.
